<!-/Post: 323-!>
<!-Post: 324-!><!-Time: 963865335-!>
<TABLE BGCOLOR=#ccffff WIDTH=60% BORDER=0 BORDERCOLOR=#0000ff> <TR><TD><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial,Helvetica" SIZE="3" COLOR="#000000"><FONT SIZE=-1> <A NAME=POST324>  By <B><!-Email-!><A HREF="javascript:alert('The e-mail address and profile information for the individual posting this message is not available.')" onMouseOver="window.status = 'The e-mail address and profile information for the individual posting this message is not available.'; return true"><!-/Email-!><!-Name-!>Patroclus<!-/Name-!></A></B> on Monday, July 17, 2000 - 04:22 pm:</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><P> <!-Text-!> BYOB- Bring Your Own Bloodstone. Clerics of any given level typically have 3 buffs to offer, one pure AC buff, one AC and Hp buff and one pure HP buff. This last Buff is referred to as the Symbol line of buffs. The first is named Symbol of Transal &#40;lvl 14&#41;. It is this buff &#40;symbol&#41; that you will most seldomly see offered.  That is because it requires a spell component to cast, a gem. These gems are sold by vendors that offer the items for the jewelry trade. And cost varying amounts of course. I am going to use round numbers in this discussion so forgive me for rounding up. The lowest symbol spell which offers the least HP of course uses a Catseye-agate, cost about 3 gp. <BR> <BR>At lvl 24 Symbol of Ryltan uses a Bloodstone, cost 6 gp, at lvl 34 Symbol of Pinzarn uses Jasper, cost 1pp. It is my policy to cast these spells on the pullers only and/or on kin that I am taking extra special care of and lastly often myself. <BR> <BR>I don’t know how many of you have more then 1k pp in your bank, but I have never had 400 pp in my char’s life. One reason is the constant drain of symbol another is buying spells at each new spell circle. My latest circle cost me about 23 pp per spell. Another reason many clerics are broke is that we are often kept so manna desperate by our group we don’t come out of our spell books long enough to loot. This is most commonly a problem with FFA. <BR> <BR>Thus my suggestion, if you want your group’s CL to symbol you bring your own gems. Bring a variety of them if possible, as manna is often are real problem and lower lvl symbols are less manna intensive. <BR> <BR>Hint gems are sold in Free Port in the hall of magic. They won’t sell to dwarves unless you have done some faction work. But in the east commons at the extreme west &#40;zone border&#41; there is an inn, the eastern outer building contains a vendor lass that will deal with dwarves. <BR> <BR>To summarize: <BR>Catseye agate about 150hp cost 3gp <BR>Bloodstone about 275 hp cost 7gp <BR>Jasper about ?hp cost 1pp &#40;sorry to expensive to cast at my current level, I’ll let you know in the future&#41;. <!-/Text-!> <P> 
