<TABLE BGCOLOR=#ccffff WIDTH=60% BORDER=0 BORDERCOLOR=#0000ff> <TR><TD><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial,Helvetica" SIZE="3" COLOR="#000000"><FONT SIZE=-1> <A NAME=POST326>  By <B><!-Email-!><A HREF="mailto:worried70@hotmail.com"><!-/Email-!><!-Name-!>Badaph<!-/Name-!></A></B> on Tuesday, July 18, 2000 - 09:25 am:</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><P> <!-Text-!> Also ye will want ta symbol yer enchanters. They needs all the help they cin gets. Me uncle&#39;s highest symbol cost 12 plat each!!! So what me does is tells the group &#34;Do ye mind if me loots a few extra times ta keep our enchanter symboled?&#34; They always be saying yes so me loots more ta make up for the cost.  <BR> <BR>And nae be shy &#39;bouts gettin&#39; pasted over cause ya not getting any coins or glanders. Sometimes others be thinkin&#39; ya nae interested in them if ya just sit there all the time. Dont feel bad asking for a loot order of some type either. Its seem hard for those that dont med to see an unlooted corpse just sitting there on ther ground for very long. Sometimes they afraid someone not in yer group will come along and snatch it up. So just say yer thoughts when ya thinks they not being fair to ya. Another way to impose a semi-loot order is ta ask that everyone put split on. Then say &#40;if there are 6 people in your group&#41; that you will be looting a mob after ya see 5 splits.  <BR> <BR>Also if any of ya kin ever need a wee loan for them next circle of spells or ta gits that last bit needed fer some weapon or armor you cin ask me uncle fer a loan. Hes nae the richest cleric in the realm but he will help ya out, and me as well. <!-/Text-!> <P> 
