<!-Post: 330-!><!-Time: 963955273-!>
<TABLE BGCOLOR=#ccffff WIDTH=60% BORDER=0 BORDERCOLOR=#0000ff> <TR><TD><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial,Helvetica" SIZE="3" COLOR="#000000"><FONT SIZE=-1> <A NAME=POST330>  By <B><!-Email-!><A HREF="javascript:alert('The e-mail address and profile information for the individual posting this message is not available.')" onMouseOver="window.status = 'The e-mail address and profile information for the individual posting this message is not available.'; return true"><!-/Email-!><!-Name-!>Patroclus<!-/Name-!></A></B> on Tuesday, July 18, 2000 - 05:21 pm:</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><P> <!-Text-!> Crowd Control – Or Buying Time <BR> <BR>So there you are one happy little camper with the rest of the cowering group waiting for the one person with the guts to actually risk them selves by pulling in a dangerous MOB when low and behold the brave puller returns with a crowd! <BR> <BR>You take a moment to study the situation, your puller is being pounded, the rest of your group are assisting the puller the 2 or 3 other mobs have no dance partners, and now as your calling requires you are about to do something massively suicidal, heal the noble puller. This of course is absolutely the best way to agro the entire crowd onto your self. And suddenly you are being torn to shreds unable to cast your healing spells and causing your group to break their focus on a single MOB and spread out their attacks in an effort to save your soft skinned hide. <BR> <BR>What is the single best way to deal with this situation? One word ENCHANTER, if you are grouped with an enchanter they will quickly mesmerize all the mobs that are not the focus of your groups attack. You must keep your wits about you at a time like this, don’t wield your dainty mace in a futile effort to beat your opponents into submission because of course this will break the mesmerization.  <BR> <BR>Now you can back off and find yourself a place to sit and heal as need be. Absolutely huge “we are all dead” pulls can be safely handled in this manner nothing is better then being in a group based around having a Cleric/Enchanter Combo. <BR> <BR>Why is there never an enchanter in the house when you need one? <BR> <BR>So what to do on all those occasions when you don’t have an enchanter? Four words: Poor Man’s Crowd Control. And compared to an enchanter I mean poor, very poor. Again back to our original scenario this time with no enchanter and you are about to do something massively suicidal, but not wishing to die quickly you choose the slow road to “LOADING PLEASE WAIT”. <BR> <BR>Start by casting root on as many mobs as manna and time permits yes this will agro them but healing does too, so in for a penny in for a pound. This will buy you time, usually far less time then you need but I did say “Poor Man’s” didn’t I? <BR> <BR>If you are in a very open area and you have the spell Atone &#40;34th lvl&#41; you can pull a MOB off outside agro range root it and then back out of agro range and Atone it. Atone wipes the MOB’s hate list, thus it has just forgotten all about you and your group. And being out side agro range it will go home once root wears off. Since this plan calls for lots of specific environmental factors just forget I ever mentioned it. You will almost never be in such ideal circumstances by the time you get this spell. <BR> <BR>Now back to our crowd in the Vision™, your party is pounding on one mob and doing well thanks to your timely heals but now your root spells are getting old &#40;10 seconds later&#41; and break. So you are now swarmed, start by doing nothing. That’s right nothing! It will be easier for your taunters to taunt a mob off if you are not making it madder at you by swinging at it. The one thing you can do to help yourself is to Yaulp, as this will boost your ac slightly. Also your group will notice you are yaulping and might just re-focus on saving your hide.  <BR> <BR>Don’t panic, just take the beating. This will buy your group the time to kill off the mobs, so what was once a crowd becomes a manageable pull. Now this is where we separate the dead clerics from the almost dead clerics, two words Divine Aura &#40;17 seconds of invulnerability&#41;. Do Not Leave Home With Out It! Always have this spell Mem’d!! And have a plan for using it. The normal plan is- RUN AWAY! But often that is not an option, auxiliary option to plan one RUN TO A NICE PLACE TO DIE SO YOU CAN RETRIEVE YOUR CORPSE EASIELY. <BR> <BR>Note that if you plan on the “run away” option, make sure you cast this spell with at least 2 bubbles of health, as we all know running very slowly to the zone is just a way of dying closer to the zone. Also if grouped with a wiz make sure that you have discussed in advanced when and how Evac will be used. Because you will not be Evac’d when this spell is up.  <BR> <BR>A better plan- When your beating gets too much to bear cast Divine Aura, and then start begging for your group to TAUNT THE FLIPPING MOBS OFF YOU! Now all this should have bought your group about 60 seconds of time this is usually enough time for the group to get things under minimal control or they are going to die any way. Got manna? Hit your gate spell what the heck, ever buy a lotto ticket you might win. <BR> <BR>To summarize, start by casting root&#40;s&#41; before casting your first heal. This is the first step in buying time. Second start Yaulping but not swinging once root breaks. Sure you are losing hp but the mobs are hopefully being killed off as well. Last use your Divine Aura, and either run or hold fast. Once its down and all is lost, cast gate and pray for the words “You Regain Your Concentration And Continue Casting”. <!-/Text-!> <P> 
