<TABLE BGCOLOR=#ccffff WIDTH=60% BORDER=0 BORDERCOLOR=#0000ff> <TR><TD><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial,Helvetica" SIZE="3" COLOR="#000000"><FONT SIZE=-1> <A NAME=POST332>  By <B><!-Email-!><A HREF="javascript:alert('The e-mail address and profile information for the individual posting this message is not available.')" onMouseOver="window.status = 'The e-mail address and profile information for the individual posting this message is not available.'; return true"><!-/Email-!><!-Name-!>Badaph <!-/Name-!></A></B> on Wednesday, July 19, 2000 - 08:46 am:</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><P> <!-Text-!> Some good wurds there lad. I&#39;d like ta point out a few tactics that me good ol&#39; uncle Badaf telled me.  <BR> <BR>In yer Vison, if thar be only 1-2 extra mobs on the puller, what me uncle does is first move a decent distance off from the group, then heal ASAP. This will cause them ta run at ya. Then ya root them there. Seems when ya root them mobs at the puller then says &#34;Git back! Thems rooted now!&#34; no one seems ta listen to ya. Guess cause yer words are often lost in they extictment and spam of battle. So you just end up wasting mana since the rooted mobs are still smackin the tar out of the puller. Also remember that rooting and no-damage stuns do not break mez.   <BR> <BR>Also if you gots an evac, always remember you can make yer DA spell end at any time you want. All ya do is click on the icon and it ends the spell. <BR> <BR>Atone. Sometimes this spell dont werk when ya cast it. But ya wont know it nae work from the message. Its always the same whether the mob forgot about ya or not, something like &#34;The mob calms down.&#34;.  As Pat pointed out it werks best in outdoor situations where ya gots a lot of room. If you are in this setting heres what ya do. Take the mob away from the group. Root &#39;em. Get back out of his normal agro range. Cast Atone. Then ya do a check to see ifun it werked. What ya do is move of to the left or right &#40;strafing is the best method&#41;. If the mob is still agroed he will turn toward you. If he keeps looking ahead hes forgot about ya. Sometimes you will know right away if he forgets cause he will turn away from ya as soon as it hits him. If he keeps facing ya cast it some again. Seafury cyclops is the place where me uncle used this spell ALOT. But also to some extent in Sol B as well. <!-/Text-!> <P> 
