<TABLE BGCOLOR=#ccffff WIDTH=60% BORDER=0 BORDERCOLOR=#0000ff> <TR><TD><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial,Helvetica" SIZE="3" COLOR="#000000"><FONT SIZE=-1> <A NAME=POST333>  By <B><!-Email-!><A HREF="javascript:alert('The e-mail address and profile information for the individual posting this message is not available.')" onMouseOver="window.status = 'The e-mail address and profile information for the individual posting this message is not available.'; return true"><!-/Email-!><!-Name-!>Patroclus<!-/Name-!></A></B> on Thursday, July 20, 2000 - 04:46 pm:</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><P> <!-Text-!> The Masses, Myself and Mana – <BR> <BR>So what does Half mana, FM and 00m mean? At most levels &#40;maybe all, I’m only 35 so can’t say beyond&#41; clerics keep two healing spells mem’d, one Big and one small. &#40;In another post I will discuss the uses of each, here I just want to post about mana usage.&#41; <BR> <BR>A big heal costs about one bubble and a small heal costs about 1/4 of a bubble. Yes these amounts are not accurate for all levels and wisdom values. These are “round numbers” and I am rounding UP. At my current level I can cast greater healing and healing with one full bubble &#40;these are my current big and small heal&#41;. But let’s not quibble. <BR> <BR>When your cleric says half mana what this means is about 2 big heals and 2 small heals before you hear “00m med’n”. <BR> <BR>20 mana &#40;one bubble&#41; means about one big heal or several small heals. And 00m &#40;Out Of Mana&#41; means about 60 seconds of med’n for mana for a big heal. <BR> <BR>And FM &#40;Full Mana&#41; I won’t discuss because like the Loch Ness monster it doesn’t exist. <BR> <BR>So pullers keep this in mind before you go out on a hunt. <!-/Text-!> <P> 
