<TABLE BGCOLOR=#ccffff WIDTH=60% BORDER=0 BORDERCOLOR=#0000ff> <TR><TD><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial,Helvetica" SIZE="3" COLOR="#000000"><FONT SIZE=-1> <A NAME=POST336>  By <B><!-Email-!><A HREF="javascript:alert('The e-mail address and profile information for the individual posting this message is not available.')" onMouseOver="window.status = 'The e-mail address and profile information for the individual posting this message is not available.'; return true"><!-/Email-!><!-Name-!>Patroclus<!-/Name-!></A></B> on Friday, July 21, 2000 - 03:40 pm:</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><P> <!-Text-!> “I Hate Healers!” - <BR> <BR>Now when I hear folk say this I try not to take it personally, they are after all referring to MOB’s. Not to sing my own praises but in all the poles the character class most preferred for grouping is the cleric. Conversely the most hated MOB is the cleric.  <BR> <BR>Nothing causes your group to complain more then beating a mob down to near death only to have its health go shooting back up well past the half way mark. Which is why when faced with multiple pulls the words “All on the healer” are the ones first spoken. And this includes you, my fellow cleric. <BR> <BR>Get your nose out of your spell book and report for battle cleric duty. If you are working an area where there are MOB clerics it is crucial you keep Holy Might &#40;lvl19 stun spell&#41; at the ready. And if possible Stun &#40;lvl 5&#41;. The stun line of spells are used to interrupt casters. <BR> <BR>It is crucial that the MOB cleric is prevented from healing and timing is crucial. Get your dainty mace out and position your self where you have a good view of the MOB Cleric’s hands. When you see the blue sparks begin to appear from its hands hit either of your stun spells. Your reaction time is crucial, healing’s cast time is about 3.75 and the casting time for Holy Might 2.0. By the time you see the blue sparks emanating and move your mouse over your spell gem you are probably already too late. Best thing to do is set up a hot-key, second best keep your mouse hovering over the stun spell gem. <BR> <BR>Now recovery time on Holy Might is 18 seconds, that’s why if possible you need Stun mem’d. Because a second heal is surely on the way, but my personal experience has been that keeping a second stun spell on hand is rare and difficult.  <BR> <BR>So Battle Cleric I tell you this, “Dead MOB’s don’t wear plaid- kill, Kill, KILL!” It didn’t cast heal the first time because it was feeling healthy, so during the duration of your stun, its time to open up with both barrels and hit it with any and every offensive spell you have. You have the duration of the stun and the 3.75 seconds it takes for it to cast heal for you to dispatch it, so that it won’t ever be casting heal again. <BR> <BR>Once dispatched you can again return to the quiet of your spell book and the healing of your group, battle cleric duty has ended. <BR> <BR>I will close by saying thank the lords that the game’s AI doesn’t apply this, or the highest-level cleric pc would be level 2! <!-/Text-!> <P> 
