<TABLE BGCOLOR=#ccffff WIDTH=60% BORDER=0 BORDERCOLOR=#0000ff> <TR><TD><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial,Helvetica" SIZE="3" COLOR="#000000"><FONT SIZE=-1> <A NAME=POST1151>  By <B><!-Email-!><A HREF="javascript:alert('The e-mail address and profile information for the individual posting this message is not available.')" onMouseOver="window.status = 'The e-mail address and profile information for the individual posting this message is not available.'; return true"><!-/Email-!><!-Name-!>Patorclus<!-/Name-!></A></B> on Friday, June 22, 2001 - 04:58 pm:</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><P> <!-Text-!> Greetings! <BR> <BR>I would like to tell you of my journeys last eve, indeed words fail me but I will try to write of it all the same… <BR> <BR>My companions, Strings &#40;bard&#41; ,Carpaythian Shadows &#40;rogue&#41;, Kamelyon &#40;enchanter, par excellence!&#41;  and others who came and went in the course of the eve formed a Dreadlands squad the likes of which I have never seen, nor even heard of before. <BR> <BR>O’ dear reader, you ask what could possibly be differing from all other groups that perpetually camp the four walls of Karanor’s Castle? My answer two words “train pulling”. To be sure I have been in aggressive groups before in which it was not uncommon to pull two at a time, but those battles were often hard fought and all to often would end up being touch and go affairs but… <BR> <BR>Our heroic pullers &#40;Carpaythian mostly&#41;, would go out and deliberately pull three or more mobs. Yes I said or more! I couldn’t tell you our record pull, but if some one spoke of seven mobs in one pull I would not question it. Now you would think that such pulls would leave the dear cleric mana desperate pulling hair from his head trying to med up for a lone heal before the grouped was wiped out. <BR> <BR>But no, not with the amazing Mez’ work provided by Kamelyon and the song twisting of Strings. I was seldom under a bubble of mana and indeed spent much mana nuk’ing mobs. In fact during one slow period when we were tankless, Pat even had a brief moment in which he tanked in order to provide a taunt for Carpaythian to back-stab from. <BR> <BR>There were zero deaths and we spent hours and hours at this. Never have I seen the like! <BR> <BR>My thanks to The Protectorate for having me along last eve. Truly wondrous! <BR> <BR>Patroclus Kuldmorndin &#40;Cleric&#41; <BR>Clan Axepeak <!-/Text-!> <P> 
